text: Okay, so you guys decided to make an interesting backstory for Silver in Angry Birds 2 the game but decide to just throw out Silver's entire origin and just make her Chuck's sister? This honestly makes zero sense why you guys are just changing up everything and not sticking to what people already loved in the games. I understand when the plot of the movie is changed and all, but it's gotten to the point where you're altering already existing characters. A great example of this is Mighty Eagle: In the games, he was known as a mysterious legend that could defeat anyone in his path without problems, but in the movie, you made him look like a complete loser who just sits around and doesn't do what he was known for. I think this movie would be a whole lot better if you just stick to what was already established in the games with the characters at least. Sure, adding new things to the movie ain't a bad thing, in fact, it can be good if done correctly. The problem is that you're altering what was already established in the games. If it ain't broke, don't fix it.
